original: Berglund, Nils Emil, hovrättsfiskal, Jönköping, f. 27/2/12 i Hösisna, Älvsb. 1, av domprost Emil B. o. Elilen Myr-sten. — Stud:ex. i Skara 32, jur. kand. i Upps. 37. Tingstjg. i Skåmngs, Valle o. Vilske doms. 37-40, fiskal i Göta hovr. 41, tingssekreterare i Skövde domis. 44-47, hovr:fiskai i Jömköp. s>ed. 47.
translated: Berglund, Nils Emil was a court fiscal in Jönköping. He was born on February 27, 1912 in Hösisna, Älvsborgs län, to the cathedral provost Emil B. and Elilen Myr-sten. He completed his high school education in Skara in 1932, and earned a law degree from Uppsala University in 1937. He served as a court clerk in Skåmngs, Valle, and Vilske from 1937 to 1940, and then as a fiscal in Göta Court of Appeals in 1941. From 1944 to 1947, he was a court secretary in Skövde. In 1947, he became a court fiscal in Jönköping, where he remained until an unspecified year.
